<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="b1946_12_08_an_OffenerBrief"><teiHeader><fileDesc> <titleStmt> <title>Von <persName key="WittgensteinLudwig" role="sender" full="yes">Ludwig Wittgenstein</persName> Offener Brief, 8. 12. 1946</title> <author>Wittgenstein, Ludwig</author> </titleStmt> <editionStmt n="bw2"> <edition>2. Auflage</edition> </editionStmt> <publicationStmt> <p>Ludwig Wittgenstein: Gesamtbriefwechsel, 2. Auflage</p> </publicationStmt> <sourceDesc default="false"> <p>Abschrift McGuinness.</p> </sourceDesc> </fileDesc><encodingDesc><p>TEI P5</p></encodingDesc><revisionDesc><list type="simple"><item>2010/05/15: Added to the collection</item><item>2018/12: Added to Innsbruck Correspondence Edition</item></list></revisionDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div type="transcript" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"> <div type="maintext" org="uniform" sample="complete" part="N"> <p rend="left">Testimonial:</p> <p rend="indent">I have known Mr Rowland Hutt intimately for about 14 years. I made his acquaintance when he came to my philosophical classes for a few terms, &amp; since then I have always been in friendly contact with him. He has an excellent intellect &amp; is an exceedingly kind, serious &amp; conscientious man. I feel sure that he will have a genuinely good influence on the character of his pupils.</p> <p rend="indent">L.Wittgenstein</p> </div> <div type="postscript" org="uniform" sample="complete" part="N"> <p rend="indent">Trinity College </p> <p rend="indent">Cambridge </p> <p rend="indent">8.12.46 </p> </div> </div></body></text></TEI>